1
00:00:09,248 --> 00:00:14,123
(This program is intended for mature audiences.
It may feature explicit content, violence, and strong language)

2
00:00:14,156 --> 00:00:19,959
(All characters, places, and events
in this series are entirely fictitious)

3
00:01:16,597 --> 00:01:17,828
Why are you up so early?

4
00:01:19,397 --> 00:01:20,594
I've got to head to work.

5
00:01:21,283 --> 00:01:24,624
At first, I thought I'd leave quietly.

6
00:01:25,460 --> 00:01:28,169
But I was worried you'd wake up
and not find me.

7
00:01:28,666 --> 00:01:29,840
So I thought I'd let you know first.

8
00:01:35,857 --> 00:01:36,602
Go back to sleep, okay?

9
00:01:41,569 --> 00:01:42,213
Hmm.

10
00:01:44,900 --> 00:01:46,187
Being this sweet...

11
00:01:46,932 --> 00:01:48,253
Do you want some morning intimacy?

12
00:01:49,709 --> 00:01:52,283
No, I didn't budget time for that.

13
00:01:53,118 --> 00:01:53,886
Rain check for now.

14
00:01:55,106 --> 00:01:57,120
Police's Boyfriend 101.

15
00:01:57,312 --> 00:01:58,548
(Police's Boyfriend 101:
Make peace with the schedule)

16
00:01:58,548 --> 00:02:00,354
Make peace with the schedule.

17
00:02:01,992 --> 00:02:03,245
That's not the only rule.

18
00:02:03,584 --> 00:02:04,893
There are plenty more.

19
00:02:05,762 --> 00:02:06,846
You'll learn them one by one.

20
00:02:08,652 --> 00:02:11,554
Oh, right, here's your key card.

21
00:02:12,875 --> 00:02:13,552
I'm off.

22
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:56,128
(New post)
(Police's Boyfriend 101.)

23
00:02:56,128 --> 00:02:58,924
(Bring it on. Ready for all the rules!)

24
00:03:09,006 --> 00:03:11,328
(Tai Moonlit)
(Darn, you move fast.)

25
00:03:13,464 --> 00:03:16,320
(It doesn't count as fast
when it's with my boyfriend.)

26
00:03:16,320 --> 00:03:19,392
(Wayu)

27
00:03:39,193 --> 00:03:43,279
=Love of Silom=

28
00:03:44,544 --> 00:03:47,872
(Phat Phong Road, Bang Rak District)

29
00:03:55,438 --> 00:03:57,075
- What's up, man?
- Umm.

30
00:03:57,335 --> 00:03:59,796
You've got a boyfriend now.
Shouldn't you be more excited?

31
00:04:00,936 --> 00:04:02,833
I was, at first.

32
00:04:04,165 --> 00:04:08,093
But I've been texting him all day
and he hasn't replied once.

33
00:04:08,963 --> 00:04:11,672
I had no idea cops could be this busy.

34
00:04:13,535 --> 00:04:14,449
Not replying to chats.

35
00:04:15,454 --> 00:04:16,447
Then call him.

36
00:04:17,102 --> 00:04:19,134
Just talk for a minute or two.

37
00:04:19,270 --> 00:04:21,505
The criminal won't run away, right?

38
00:04:21,697 --> 00:04:23,289
Hehe.

39
00:04:23,289 --> 00:04:24,632
Got you at last.

40
00:04:24,632 --> 00:04:25,998
Those terrible criminals.

41
00:04:25,998 --> 00:04:29,351
All the victims were good-looking guys.

42
00:04:29,475 --> 00:04:31,090
Hey, look.

43
00:04:31,124 --> 00:04:33,586
Seems like they only
target night workers.

44
00:04:33,586 --> 00:04:35,437
(It's been confirmed to be linked
to a human trafficking case.)

45
00:04:35,437 --> 00:04:37,908
(Mr. Chainphop is now being
transferred to prison.)

46
00:04:37,908 --> 00:04:40,223
(Stay tuned for the latest updates
from our field reporters.)

47
00:04:40,223 --> 00:04:41,440
(Breaking news: Drug ring linked to)
(We're reporting live)

48
00:04:41,440 --> 00:04:43,124
(a human trafficking network busted)
(from the scene.)

49
00:04:43,124 --> 00:04:44,672
(Police have raided and arrested)

50
00:04:44,672 --> 00:04:46,228
- (a major drug ring.)
- Hey.

51
00:04:46,228 --> 00:04:49,480
That Chain, wasn't he your old client?

52
00:04:49,480 --> 00:04:51,636
Hey, he wasn't my client.

53
00:04:51,862 --> 00:04:53,420
He was Sky's client.

54
00:04:54,436 --> 00:04:55,531
But honestly,

55
00:04:56,468 --> 00:04:59,019
I almost ended up
one of his victims too.

56
00:05:01,605 --> 00:05:03,129
This really shook me up.

57
00:05:04,619 --> 00:05:07,419
I think that's a pretty good reason
to call your boyfriend.

58
00:05:09,699 --> 00:05:12,013
Your boyfriend's the cop
working this case, isn't he?

59
00:05:14,813 --> 00:05:15,412
Call him.

60
00:05:17,726 --> 00:05:19,102
Go on. Call him.

61
00:05:26,012 --> 00:05:29,489
Look at you, grinning ear to ear.

62
00:05:30,054 --> 00:05:32,560
Got you.

63
00:05:33,858 --> 00:05:35,247
- Give me another draft, Lieutenant.
- Yes, sir.

64
00:05:39,264 --> 00:05:42,400
(Wayu)

65
00:05:43,206 --> 00:05:45,373
Hello, is this a good time, Krit?

66
00:05:45,768 --> 00:05:47,281
Am I interrupting?

67
00:05:47,620 --> 00:05:49,347
I can talk. What's up?

68
00:05:50,273 --> 00:05:56,121
I just saw the news that Chain
was arrested and already confessed.

69
00:05:56,121 --> 00:05:58,424
Does that mean the case will be closed?

70
00:05:58,762 --> 00:06:02,262
Not yet. They're very cautious.
There's been no movement at all.

71
00:06:02,623 --> 00:06:04,859
Emm. I see.

72
00:06:04,859 --> 00:06:08,968
There's been no word about the parties either.
Everything seems quiet.

73
00:06:09,882 --> 00:06:13,235
We still need to be careful.
It could be the calm before the storm.

74
00:06:13,879 --> 00:06:16,340
Oh, and...

75
00:06:16,758 --> 00:06:19,478
What time will you be back?

76
00:06:21,070 --> 00:06:23,847
You called just to ask me that?

77
00:06:26,512 --> 00:06:30,576
I got worried. You didn't reply
to any of my texts all day.

78
00:06:32,021 --> 00:06:32,935
I've been busy.

79
00:06:34,990 --> 00:06:35,983
You've been waiting for me, haven't you?

80
00:06:36,525 --> 00:06:37,857
Oh, no, it's fine.

81
00:06:38,693 --> 00:06:41,447
So, what time will you be back?

82
00:06:42,983 --> 00:06:44,608
Late. What about you, Wayu?

83
00:06:45,060 --> 00:06:46,968
Oh, I'll probably be even later.

84
00:06:47,081 --> 00:06:50,942
Around 3 to 4 AM,
unless a client books me out.

85
00:06:52,691 --> 00:06:54,035
Then don't let them book you.

86
00:06:54,656 --> 00:06:56,552
And keep your distance too.

87
00:06:59,002 --> 00:06:59,883
Captain.

88
00:07:00,617 --> 00:07:05,234
(Host's Boyfriend 101: Don't be jealous of clients)
Host's Boyfriend 101: Don't be jealous of clients.

89
00:07:08,666 --> 00:07:09,467
Captain.

90
00:07:10,246 --> 00:07:11,646
Mr. Supanut is here.

91
00:07:11,974 --> 00:07:14,288
- Okay. I'll be right there.
- Yes, sir.

92
00:07:16,309 --> 00:07:19,063
Alright, I'll see you at the room, then.

93
00:07:20,373 --> 00:07:21,005
Yeah.

94
00:07:42,985 --> 00:07:45,435
This was the night Captain caught
the criminal at the pier.

95
00:07:45,920 --> 00:07:47,580
(Mr. Supanut was at home the whole time)

96
00:07:47,625 --> 00:07:50,899
(Went inside at 8:30 PM
and didn't come out until the morning)

97
00:07:54,523 --> 00:07:55,844
Finished work at 5PM.

98
00:07:56,295 --> 00:07:57,661
But got home at 8:30 PM?

99
00:07:59,061 --> 00:07:59,942
Officer.

100
00:08:00,653 --> 00:08:02,866
This is Bangkok. You get off at 5 PM,

101
00:08:02,866 --> 00:08:05,338
grab dinner on the way,
and get home by 8:30 PM.

102
00:08:05,338 --> 00:08:06,642
That's already pretty fast.

103
00:08:07,585 --> 00:08:09,018
If you don't believe me, Captain,

104
00:08:09,493 --> 00:08:12,541
you can call in Mr. Supanut's friends
for more questioning.

105
00:08:12,992 --> 00:08:16,526
He was having dinner with them
at the time.

106
00:08:18,073 --> 00:08:18,931
Thank you.

107
00:08:21,538 --> 00:08:24,824
I'm assuring you with complete honesty.

108
00:08:25,173 --> 00:08:28,978
Are you really still going to arrest me?
Let me go to earn a living.

109
00:08:29,272 --> 00:08:31,191
Then how do you know
about Mr. Chain's port?

110
00:08:33,708 --> 00:08:37,411
As a producer, why would you need
to go to the port?

111
00:08:37,637 --> 00:08:38,563
Am I right?

112
00:08:41,588 --> 00:08:43,688
Mr. Supanut is in business.

113
00:08:44,591 --> 00:08:46,420
He has goods shipped in from China.

114
00:08:46,623 --> 00:08:48,723
So he had them sent
through Mr. Chainphop's port.

115
00:08:50,586 --> 00:08:51,974
But there's no evidence of that.

116
00:08:52,494 --> 00:08:54,379
That Mr. Supanut transferred
money to Mr. Chain.

117
00:08:54,616 --> 00:08:56,750
It's only Mr. Chain who transferred
money to Mr. Supanut.

118
00:08:57,913 --> 00:08:59,606
Mr. Chainphop used a different account.

119
00:09:01,277 --> 00:09:03,456
Mr. Supanut transferred
into this account.

120
00:09:08,524 --> 00:09:09,270
Sigh.

121
00:09:12,512 --> 00:09:14,880
(Supanut Tosakarn, Chainphop Udomdirek)

122
00:09:18,016 --> 00:09:19,584
(Supanut Tosakarn, Chainphop Udomdirek)

123
00:09:22,557 --> 00:09:24,589
But there's evidence
of transfer only three times.

124
00:09:24,589 --> 00:09:27,863
Why? Was the business unsuccessful?

125
00:09:30,855 --> 00:09:32,424
Business has risks.

126
00:09:32,616 --> 00:09:34,817
My production line has quality issues.

127
00:09:34,817 --> 00:09:38,407
So I had to stop, and Chain
gradually transferred the money back.

128
00:09:39,852 --> 00:09:40,801
Here it is.

129
00:09:41,884 --> 00:09:45,734
Here's the contract Mr. Supanut signed
before working with Mr. Chainphop.

130
00:09:46,705 --> 00:09:48,760
It states that if the goods
are not transported,

131
00:09:48,918 --> 00:09:50,216
the money will be refunded.

132
00:09:51,063 --> 00:09:53,445
And Mr. Chainphop refunded
according to the contract.

133
00:09:59,586 --> 00:10:00,376
Mm.

134
00:10:29,638 --> 00:10:31,489
There's been no movement yet, Captain.

135
00:10:32,167 --> 00:10:32,833
Mm.

136
00:10:33,951 --> 00:10:35,776
Hello.

137
00:10:35,776 --> 00:10:37,823
I miss you so much.

138
00:10:37,823 --> 00:10:42,271
- I miss you too.
- Today... You look really handsome.

139
00:10:42,271 --> 00:10:43,863
- Thanks.
- I'm back.

140
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:50,880
Cheers!

141
00:10:53,248 --> 00:10:54,592
(K)

142
00:11:00,729 --> 00:11:02,272
(K)
Let's dance.

143
00:11:02,368 --> 00:11:04,320
- Let's dance.
- Let's dance. Come on.

144
00:11:19,680 --> 00:11:20,992
Please, go ahead

145
00:11:21,056 --> 00:11:23,093
Whoa. Slowly walk.

146
00:11:23,093 --> 00:11:25,114
- Slowly walk.
- Hmm.

147
00:11:25,114 --> 00:11:26,119
Hello.

148
00:11:26,400 --> 00:11:27,424
Hello.

149
00:11:27,520 --> 00:11:29,359
Wayu.

150
00:11:29,821 --> 00:11:32,350
- I'm heading back first.
- Oh.

151
00:11:32,757 --> 00:11:35,545
Ouch.

152
00:11:35,545 --> 00:11:37,344
- Bye-bye.
- Bye-bye.

153
00:11:37,376 --> 00:11:39,700
- Sweet dreams.
- Sweet dreams.

154
00:11:39,808 --> 00:11:41,760
See you, Niao.

155
00:11:41,760 --> 00:11:43,357
See you.

156
00:11:43,798 --> 00:11:46,496
See you, Niao. Sweet dreams.

157
00:12:24,304 --> 00:12:25,433
Back now, Krit.

158
00:12:41,588 --> 00:12:43,281
Krit.

159
00:12:47,605 --> 00:12:48,305
Krit.

160
00:13:09,676 --> 00:13:10,432
Krit.

161
00:13:11,628 --> 00:13:13,219
Sorry for coming back late.

162
00:13:13,931 --> 00:13:17,363
My client just wouldn't go home.
No matter what, he wouldn't leave.

163
00:13:17,375 --> 00:13:18,199
And then...

164
00:13:18,481 --> 00:13:21,868
I was so busy I couldn't even check
my phone. Everything was chaos.

165
00:13:22,760 --> 00:13:23,437
Mm.

166
00:13:24,837 --> 00:13:25,413
Hey.

167
00:13:26,169 --> 00:13:27,716
You're not mad at me, are you?

168
00:13:29,974 --> 00:13:31,080
How could I be?

169
00:13:31,859 --> 00:13:34,185
I saw how wasted
your client was last night.

170
00:13:34,512 --> 00:13:35,223
Huh?

171
00:13:36,578 --> 00:13:38,000
I stopped by your place last night.

172
00:13:47,495 --> 00:13:50,306
Oh. Hehe.

173
00:13:50,464 --> 00:13:53,472
Emm...

174
00:13:54,607 --> 00:13:55,792
Just leave him be.

175
00:13:55,792 --> 00:13:58,773
Wayu can really take care of himself.

176
00:13:59,969 --> 00:14:01,516
- But...
- Hmm.

177
00:14:02,430 --> 00:14:05,524
Trust me, Captain. You should head back.

178
00:14:05,749 --> 00:14:07,567
Wayu knows how to handle himself.

179
00:14:07,691 --> 00:14:11,067
If you keep hovering like this,
he won't be able to work.

180
00:14:13,166 --> 00:14:15,819
Oh... Tickle...

181
00:14:15,819 --> 00:14:17,152
Ah! Oh.

182
00:14:17,547 --> 00:14:19,545
Are you okay, Niao?

183
00:14:19,616 --> 00:14:21,056
I'm fine.

184
00:14:21,056 --> 00:14:22,254
Come on, drink up.

185
00:14:22,548 --> 00:14:24,094
(At first, I was going to pick you up.)

186
00:14:24,648 --> 00:14:25,393
(But...)

187
00:14:26,578 --> 00:14:28,520
I saw you were busy working,
so I didn't want to bother you.

188
00:14:29,807 --> 00:14:33,634
I thought you were mad at me.
I couldn't find you in the room.

189
00:14:33,634 --> 00:14:35,206
And you didn't answer my calls.

190
00:14:36,355 --> 00:14:40,599
I was about to go work out.
But when you said you were back,

191
00:14:40,791 --> 00:14:41,898
I just turned the car back.

192
00:14:43,151 --> 00:14:44,110
So we could meet.

193
00:14:47,181 --> 00:14:48,321
Hmm.

194
00:14:49,349 --> 00:14:51,528
Sorry for making you worry.

195
00:14:52,521 --> 00:14:53,277
Okay?

196
00:14:54,147 --> 00:14:56,122
Hmm, go.

197
00:14:56,551 --> 00:14:58,019
Go shower and get some rest.

198
00:14:58,516 --> 00:14:59,148
Hmm?

199
00:14:59,656 --> 00:15:00,378
Hmm?

200
00:15:02,275 --> 00:15:04,917
It's not just cops
who need to stay in shape.

201
00:15:05,684 --> 00:15:07,287
My job requires it too.

202
00:15:07,581 --> 00:15:08,631
Come on. I'm going with you.

203
00:15:09,444 --> 00:15:10,967
But you haven't slept at all yet.

204
00:15:11,634 --> 00:15:13,982
It's okay. I can sleep later.

205
00:15:14,242 --> 00:15:15,833
I just want to spend time together.

206
00:15:17,606 --> 00:15:20,056
Go on ahead. Give me a sec to change.

207
00:15:20,056 --> 00:15:21,128
Go on, hurry. Go.

208
00:15:26,107 --> 00:15:28,421
♪There's no one else♪

209
00:15:28,421 --> 00:15:34,392
♪Who could make me fall
this hard like you do♪

210
00:15:34,392 --> 00:15:36,960
Hmm, you little troublemaker.

211
00:15:37,543 --> 00:15:39,616
- Hey, Wayu...
- Ah!

212
00:15:41,776 --> 00:15:42,576
(Police's Boyfriend 101)

213
00:15:42,576 --> 00:15:44,000
(1. Make peace with the schedule;
2. Don't get mad if he replies late on Line)

214
00:15:46,213 --> 00:15:47,071
Oops.

215
00:15:49,148 --> 00:15:50,740
What is up with you, Tai?

216
00:15:50,943 --> 00:15:52,637
- Hey!
- Hey!

217
00:15:53,641 --> 00:15:55,188
Calm down first, will you?

218
00:15:55,560 --> 00:15:57,705
Talk to Wayu some other day.

219
00:15:57,796 --> 00:16:00,099
He's only just started being happy.

220
00:16:00,957 --> 00:16:02,436
So now you're taking his side too?

221
00:16:02,921 --> 00:16:07,741
I told you, you can have a boyfriend.
Just don't let it affect the job.

222
00:16:07,741 --> 00:16:10,937
He's not even drinking with the clients.
Sales are tanking.

223
00:16:10,937 --> 00:16:12,833
You still want me to keep him on?

224
00:16:13,646 --> 00:16:14,199
Hey!

225
00:16:15,509 --> 00:16:16,197
Ow.

226
00:16:16,875 --> 00:16:18,602
Just cut him some slack for now.

227
00:16:18,602 --> 00:16:23,490
He's just into his boyfriend right now,
not trying to let work suffer.

228
00:16:24,043 --> 00:16:25,263
- No way.
- Hey!

229
00:16:26,290 --> 00:16:28,277
Hey! Hmm...

230
00:16:29,553 --> 00:16:33,188
Come on, Tai. I need to talk to him.

231
00:16:33,730 --> 00:16:34,430
Hey!

232
00:16:45,312 --> 00:16:46,976
Wow.

233
00:16:47,051 --> 00:16:48,304
Hmm.

234
00:16:52,063 --> 00:16:55,891
If you scold him, it's not going to
increase the sales number.

235
00:16:56,726 --> 00:17:00,316
In fact, he might
not even work here anymore.

236
00:17:03,071 --> 00:17:03,782
Yeah.

237
00:17:04,414 --> 00:17:06,243
Just make sure
he doesn't end up heartbroken.

238
00:17:06,683 --> 00:17:08,207
Or we'll all be done.

239
00:17:08,647 --> 00:17:11,978
And remind him,
whether he's the top host or not,

240
00:17:11,978 --> 00:17:13,614
I can still fire him.

241
00:17:17,600 --> 00:17:18,208
Can I go now?

242
00:17:18,208 --> 00:17:19,587
Uh... Yes, you can go now.

243
00:17:32,608 --> 00:17:34,816
Darn, Tai. You're really
going for Madam now?

244
00:17:34,816 --> 00:17:37,322
No wonder older women
and widows adore you.

245
00:17:37,322 --> 00:17:38,553
Aw, Richy.

246
00:17:39,321 --> 00:17:40,698
Keep it up and you're next.

247
00:17:41,477 --> 00:17:44,107
Get lost. Just get away from me.

248
00:17:44,960 --> 00:17:45,664
Go.

249
00:17:46,208 --> 00:17:47,042
Messing with Madam?

250
00:17:49,853 --> 00:17:52,236
Ugh, what am I doing here?

251
00:18:02,531 --> 00:18:03,435
Heading home already?

252
00:18:04,789 --> 00:18:06,212
You're leaving early these days.

253
00:18:09,102 --> 00:18:10,332
Oh, Foei.

254
00:18:10,581 --> 00:18:13,640
Well, it's just a regular weekday,
and there aren't many customers.

255
00:18:13,866 --> 00:18:15,243
So I'm heading home.

256
00:18:16,880 --> 00:18:18,540
Not because your boyfriend's
waiting for you at home?

257
00:18:20,312 --> 00:18:21,983
How did you know
I have a boyfriend, Foei?

258
00:18:24,986 --> 00:18:26,792
Oh, Tai.

259
00:18:27,334 --> 00:18:28,813
Wow, darn.

260
00:18:28,937 --> 00:18:30,868
If Tai knows, the whole world knows.

261
00:18:32,358 --> 00:18:33,521
It's because of that Captain.

262
00:18:34,085 --> 00:18:38,363
He comes to see you at the bar
every day. How could I not know?

263
00:18:38,759 --> 00:18:40,170
Aw, Foei.

264
00:18:40,170 --> 00:18:41,581
You don't have to worry.

265
00:18:41,581 --> 00:18:44,821
I promise I won't let it affect my work.

266
00:18:44,821 --> 00:18:45,728
You can trust me.

267
00:18:45,728 --> 00:18:47,237
Won't affect it? Lie!

268
00:18:47,497 --> 00:18:48,987
I had to come out and say this

269
00:18:48,987 --> 00:18:51,245
because it's affecting your work.

270
00:18:55,365 --> 00:18:56,539
I'll be straight with you.

271
00:18:58,346 --> 00:18:59,746
Do you think that Captain

272
00:18:59,746 --> 00:19:01,428
will really take you seriously?

273
00:19:03,990 --> 00:19:05,853
Do you think someone in this kind of job

274
00:19:06,260 --> 00:19:08,924
will be loved like a normal person?

275
00:19:14,173 --> 00:19:16,972
If you date someone, choose carefully.

276
00:19:17,430 --> 00:19:18,875
Don't let them deceive you.

277
00:19:19,965 --> 00:19:21,365
And don't let him come to the bar.

278
00:19:21,839 --> 00:19:25,677
If the regulars see him,
you'll be in trouble.

279
00:19:27,088 --> 00:19:28,703
You're on a roll right now.

280
00:19:29,166 --> 00:19:31,231
Don't forget why you got
into this line of work.

281
00:19:34,426 --> 00:19:35,668
Got it, Foei.

282
00:20:05,088 --> 00:20:05,822
Hey, Krit.

283
00:20:06,228 --> 00:20:08,768
I've told you
not to pick me up. It's late.

284
00:20:09,062 --> 00:20:11,929
So I don't want you going back alone.

285
00:20:13,487 --> 00:20:15,429
Listen, Krit, let me tell you something.

286
00:20:15,429 --> 00:20:18,025
If someone sees us, it'll cause trouble.

287
00:20:18,025 --> 00:20:20,679
You know it's not just beauty queens
who have drama, right?

288
00:20:20,882 --> 00:20:22,790
There's drama in the host bar world too.

289
00:20:23,399 --> 00:20:24,506
Are you going to keep complaining?

290
00:20:26,177 --> 00:20:27,689
Have you seen
what I prepared for you yet?

291
00:20:29,902 --> 00:20:30,805
What is it?

292
00:20:35,851 --> 00:20:36,630
Hey!

293
00:20:50,240 --> 00:20:54,434
Wow, behind that serious face,

294
00:20:54,547 --> 00:20:56,296
who knew you'd celebrate
a three-day anniversary?

295
00:20:57,245 --> 00:20:58,893
It's not any anniversary.

296
00:20:59,186 --> 00:21:01,693
Just... wanted to give you something.

297
00:21:03,200 --> 00:21:03,872
Whoa.

298
00:21:05,576 --> 00:21:06,152
Hey.

299
00:21:07,292 --> 00:21:07,981
Wow, then...

300
00:21:09,527 --> 00:21:12,903
One, two, three... Why are there
so many flowers?

301
00:21:12,903 --> 00:21:14,709
Is this almost every kind of flower?

302
00:21:15,172 --> 00:21:17,769
Well, I didn't know
which flowers you liked,

303
00:21:18,198 --> 00:21:20,207
so I told the shop to put in every kind.

304
00:21:20,625 --> 00:21:22,228
And it turned out pretty nice.

305
00:21:30,063 --> 00:21:33,111
But flowers wilt so quickly.

306
00:21:33,461 --> 00:21:35,414
Honestly, it feels like
a waste of money.

307
00:21:37,378 --> 00:21:38,281
But do you like it?

308
00:21:40,788 --> 00:21:43,610
If you like it, nothing's too expensive.

309
00:21:45,111 --> 00:21:48,216
Wow, showing off, aren't you?

310
00:21:53,251 --> 00:21:54,764
Come on, let's take a picture.

311
00:21:55,339 --> 00:21:57,326
I want to keep a picture.

312
00:22:00,250 --> 00:22:00,860
Ugh.

313
00:22:02,847 --> 00:22:03,965
Here we go.

314
00:22:05,410 --> 00:22:07,329
One, two, three.

315
00:22:09,395 --> 00:22:10,151
Oops.

316
00:22:11,099 --> 00:22:12,093
That's all I could do.

317
00:22:15,310 --> 00:22:17,862
Let's do it again. Smile a bit,
please. Smile first.

318
00:22:18,460 --> 00:22:21,677
One, two, three.

319
00:22:24,421 --> 00:22:25,550
You can't post it.

320
00:22:26,543 --> 00:22:27,435
Why not?

321
00:22:30,427 --> 00:22:32,131
Rule number 3
of being a police's boyfriend.

322
00:22:33,305 --> 00:22:34,965
Be good at keeping official secrets.

323
00:22:36,071 --> 00:22:38,916
But it's just posting pictures, right?
What's the big deal?

324
00:22:39,842 --> 00:22:41,626
Social media's scary these days.

325
00:22:42,382 --> 00:22:45,701
Imagine if criminals become aware
because of these pictures,

326
00:22:46,062 --> 00:22:46,796
what will we do?

327
00:22:48,873 --> 00:22:51,222
Understood, Officer.

328
00:22:51,628 --> 00:22:55,094
Don't worry about it. I'm very good
at keeping secrets.

329
00:22:55,399 --> 00:22:56,708
Even if I post it,

330
00:22:57,103 --> 00:22:59,305
no one will see it anyway
because I use a burner account.

331
00:22:59,508 --> 00:23:00,242
What is that?

332
00:23:01,190 --> 00:23:02,342
You have a burner account?

333
00:23:02,703 --> 00:23:04,283
- Hmm.
- Why didn't I know about it?

334
00:23:04,814 --> 00:23:09,003
I've got a burner account for whenever
I want to save photos or moments.

335
00:23:09,003 --> 00:23:12,062
I post them there like a personal diary.

336
00:23:12,062 --> 00:23:12,819
But you don't have to worry.

337
00:23:12,819 --> 00:23:14,545
It's private. No one else can see it.

338
00:23:15,369 --> 00:23:18,745
The account's called SpyKongKhunPolice.

339
00:23:22,222 --> 00:23:22,865
So...

340
00:23:24,277 --> 00:23:25,462
Can I have the password too?

341
00:23:27,155 --> 00:23:28,104
Why do you want it?

342
00:23:29,684 --> 00:23:33,229
I want to post about you
and keep it as a diary too.

343
00:23:34,460 --> 00:23:35,622
Wow.

344
00:23:37,880 --> 00:23:38,569
Mm.

345
00:23:39,946 --> 00:23:40,770
Log in for me, please.

346
00:23:43,344 --> 00:23:44,676
Alright.

347
00:24:03,665 --> 00:24:05,404
Rule number 4
of being a police's boyfriend.

348
00:24:06,352 --> 00:24:08,068
Spend time with your boyfriend at home.

349
00:24:09,242 --> 00:24:10,732
Otherwise, you'll get called out
on the burner account.

350
00:24:12,629 --> 00:24:16,162
That's all about being
a police's boyfriend.

351
00:24:17,020 --> 00:24:18,657
There are only four rules?

352
00:24:19,244 --> 00:24:21,197
I thought there'd be more than that.

353
00:24:23,602 --> 00:24:25,103
Actually, there's one more.

354
00:24:26,119 --> 00:24:26,910
What is it?

355
00:24:28,423 --> 00:24:30,319
I want you to stop being an informant.

356
00:24:32,430 --> 00:24:35,862
Why? I can help you.

357
00:24:39,080 --> 00:24:40,265
It's dangerous.

358
00:24:41,044 --> 00:24:42,963
And I don't want my boyfriend
putting himself at risk.

359
00:24:43,393 --> 00:24:44,872
If anything happened to you,

360
00:24:46,124 --> 00:24:48,134
I'd blame myself.

361
00:24:50,391 --> 00:24:51,204
Alright.

362
00:24:52,006 --> 00:24:54,433
Then I'll stop being your informant.

363
00:24:57,267 --> 00:25:00,078
Now it's your turn to take the test
for being a host's boyfriend.

364
00:25:01,805 --> 00:25:02,776
Is there a test too?

365
00:25:02,776 --> 00:25:04,481
Mm-hm. Here.

366
00:25:04,966 --> 00:25:06,896
Tai already told me

367
00:25:07,596 --> 00:25:10,825
what you were like that night.

368
00:25:13,298 --> 00:25:15,544
Don't worry. There are only two rules.

369
00:25:15,939 --> 00:25:19,766
First, you can't come to the bar
while I'm working.

370
00:25:20,161 --> 00:25:22,374
Because I don't want you to see it.

371
00:25:22,781 --> 00:25:26,833
But... I guess you've already seen.
There's nothing going on.

372
00:25:27,691 --> 00:25:28,730
As for the second rule,

373
00:25:29,340 --> 00:25:30,464
I have to take jobs outside the bar.

374
00:25:31,008 --> 00:25:31,648
No way.

375
00:25:32,230 --> 00:25:32,975
I'm not allowing that.

376
00:25:34,815 --> 00:25:36,982
Why would you go spend time alone
with someone else?

377
00:25:37,888 --> 00:25:38,752
Hear me out first...

378
00:25:38,752 --> 00:25:40,493
You don't need to take those jobs.

379
00:25:40,896 --> 00:25:41,984
I can make up the difference.

380
00:25:41,984 --> 00:25:43,158
No.

381
00:25:43,429 --> 00:25:46,116
I won't rely on others to the point
where I can't stand alone.

382
00:25:46,974 --> 00:25:50,936
Krit, outside jobs don't always mean
being alone with someone.

383
00:25:51,241 --> 00:25:53,002
Sometimes we go as a group.

384
00:25:53,183 --> 00:25:54,007
And another thing,

385
00:25:54,007 --> 00:25:56,998
I don't take those kinds of jobs
like you misunderstood me before.

386
00:25:57,664 --> 00:25:59,719
Just not drinking and not playing
along too much with customers

387
00:25:59,719 --> 00:26:01,842
is already enough
to get me fired by Foei.

388
00:26:02,338 --> 00:26:06,030
You want me mooching off my boyfriend
and pawning off my old stuff?

389
00:26:08,005 --> 00:26:09,191
You sell stuff too?

390
00:26:11,076 --> 00:26:15,377
Well, just brand-name items
and jewelries.

391
00:26:15,377 --> 00:26:16,879
Things customers gave me.

392
00:26:17,274 --> 00:26:19,272
But I don't really feel right
keeping them.

393
00:26:19,814 --> 00:26:24,567
If some customers don't want them back,
they tell me to just sell them.

394
00:26:25,493 --> 00:26:28,778
I hardly ever buy anything for myself.
Tai even says

395
00:26:29,060 --> 00:26:30,426
I'm stingy.

396
00:26:31,803 --> 00:26:32,865
Have you sold them all yet?

397
00:26:34,863 --> 00:26:38,814
Not yet. I'm planning
to keep them to return.

398
00:26:38,977 --> 00:26:41,569
Though I do borrow some
to wear once in a while.

399
00:26:42,308 --> 00:26:43,506
Then return every last one.

400
00:26:43,998 --> 00:26:45,327
Or just sell them all.

401
00:26:45,753 --> 00:26:48,083
If you want anything, just tell me.
I'll buy it for you.

402
00:26:48,395 --> 00:26:52,644
You should really get a condo, Wayu.
Rent it out as an investment.

403
00:26:52,644 --> 00:26:54,236
That way, you wouldn't
have to work so much.

404
00:26:55,584 --> 00:26:58,720
How about somewhere
around Thonglor or Phrom Phong?

405
00:26:58,720 --> 00:26:59,680
Krit.

406
00:27:01,308 --> 00:27:02,489
No need.

407
00:27:22,211 --> 00:27:24,295
I don't need any of that.

408
00:27:25,821 --> 00:27:28,988
Honestly, your love and attention
are enough for me.

409
00:27:30,612 --> 00:27:32,138
For someone like Captain Krit

410
00:27:33,729 --> 00:27:36,010
to be with a bar host like me,

411
00:27:38,406 --> 00:27:40,063
that alone is already beyond my dreams.

412
00:27:43,197 --> 00:27:45,002
I may not be as good as you think.

413
00:27:46,068 --> 00:27:47,020
Why?

414
00:27:49,875 --> 00:27:51,844
Are you some kind of scammer?

415
00:27:53,419 --> 00:27:56,471
Or are you the violent type?

416
00:27:56,848 --> 00:27:57,980
You mean, hit me?

417
00:27:58,336 --> 00:28:01,032
No. I'd never do that.

418
00:28:02,394 --> 00:28:04,215
Then there's nothing to worry about.

419
00:28:05,593 --> 00:28:06,414
But...

420
00:28:13,239 --> 00:28:14,765
I can't go public with this.

421
00:28:21,624 --> 00:28:22,526
Why?

422
00:28:27,219 --> 00:28:28,958
Do you have a second family
or something?

423
00:28:29,630 --> 00:28:30,894
No.

424
00:28:32,174 --> 00:28:33,798
You're the only one I'm seeing, Wayu.

425
00:28:34,914 --> 00:28:36,440
But I really can't make it public.

426
00:28:38,605 --> 00:28:40,115
Then why not?

427
00:28:44,463 --> 00:28:46,153
Why can't you tell me?

428
00:28:49,008 --> 00:28:51,010
Or do you still not trust me?

429
00:28:53,258 --> 00:28:55,702
When I'm ready, I promise

430
00:28:57,327 --> 00:28:59,164
I'll tell you everything, Wayu.

431
00:29:02,873 --> 00:29:03,792
Okay.

432
00:29:06,794 --> 00:29:08,205
Is it really okay?

433
00:29:13,258 --> 00:29:14,095
Mm-hmm.

434
00:29:16,130 --> 00:29:17,131
Because

435
00:29:17,557 --> 00:29:20,609
my line of work shouldn't reveal
that I have a partner either.

436
00:30:09,586 --> 00:30:11,850
Hmm, troublemaker. You're here already?

437
00:30:13,540 --> 00:30:14,886
Is something wrong, Foei?

438
00:30:18,643 --> 00:30:20,497
Don't tell me you're firing me.

439
00:30:21,875 --> 00:30:23,664
Foei, I'm not quitting.

440
00:30:23,664 --> 00:30:26,109
I didn't do anything wrong.
I just have a boyfriend.

441
00:30:26,109 --> 00:30:27,618
Didn't you say it was okay to have one?

442
00:30:28,045 --> 00:30:29,669
That's not what this is about.

443
00:30:29,669 --> 00:30:30,850
It's something else.

444
00:30:32,967 --> 00:30:35,346
Oh? Then what is it?

445
00:30:36,298 --> 00:30:37,594
Here, look at this.

446
00:30:41,856 --> 00:30:43,336
(The host in charge didn't take care
of things well, and didn't really entertain)

447
00:30:43,336 --> 00:30:44,732
(He was glued to his phone, and paid
no attention to customers. His name is Wayu)

448
00:30:47,936 --> 00:30:50,261
(Focusing on the client? No;
Focusing on the phone? Yes)

449
00:30:50,786 --> 00:30:52,279
Foei, I think...

450
00:30:52,525 --> 00:30:55,232
I give it my all
and care for all the customers.

451
00:30:57,250 --> 00:30:59,662
I'm sorry, Foei. The name of the bar
is mentioned too.

452
00:31:00,581 --> 00:31:04,568
I'm not blaming you. If what they said
about you online were true,

453
00:31:04,568 --> 00:31:06,767
I'd have kicked you out of the bar
a long time ago.

454
00:31:06,980 --> 00:31:09,082
Even if you've been a little distracted
because of your boyfriend,

455
00:31:09,377 --> 00:31:11,642
you've never acted the way
they accused you of.

456
00:31:14,068 --> 00:31:16,890
Do you know who did it?

457
00:31:17,547 --> 00:31:19,860
I've got a feeling it was Pete.

458
00:31:20,369 --> 00:31:22,174
That actor who used to book you.

459
00:31:22,666 --> 00:31:26,210
He even filed a back-end report
against our bar, you know.

460
00:31:26,210 --> 00:31:28,015
Saying you didn't take good care of him.

461
00:31:28,097 --> 00:31:30,656
And he badmouthed Moonlit too.

462
00:31:31,345 --> 00:31:32,740
What is his problem?

463
00:31:34,118 --> 00:31:36,563
Wayu, I'm asking you straight.

464
00:31:36,563 --> 00:31:38,565
Do you have a problem with him or not?

465
00:31:38,778 --> 00:31:41,453
The way I see it, he just hates you.

466
00:31:44,570 --> 00:31:46,047
So?

467
00:31:46,572 --> 00:31:49,098
He's really got it out for you.

468
00:31:49,098 --> 00:31:50,674
If you were me, how would you handle it?

469
00:31:53,808 --> 00:31:54,726
Well...

470
00:31:56,810 --> 00:31:59,074
Pete is Krit's ex-boyfriend.

471
00:32:00,535 --> 00:32:01,372
Hmph.

472
00:32:02,110 --> 00:32:05,490
I knew it. Your boyfriend
sounds like trouble.

473
00:32:06,245 --> 00:32:08,509
His ex is causing
this much trouble for the bar.

474
00:32:10,248 --> 00:32:12,037
You'd better watch yourself.

475
00:32:12,496 --> 00:32:14,547
He might just be using you.

476
00:32:16,467 --> 00:32:17,517
Yes, Foei.

477
00:32:18,140 --> 00:32:18,977
Give it here.

478
00:32:32,087 --> 00:32:33,071
Hello, Captain.

479
00:32:40,960 --> 00:32:42,150
(Pete)
(Has your father found out)

480
00:32:42,150 --> 00:32:43,296
(about you dating that bar host?)

481
00:32:51,497 --> 00:32:52,531
Hello.

482
00:32:54,434 --> 00:32:55,648
Let's have a talk.

483
00:32:56,977 --> 00:32:58,175
I'll send you the location in a bit.

484
00:32:58,815 --> 00:32:59,717
Okay.

485
00:33:09,299 --> 00:33:10,874
Didn't Captain just get here?

486
00:33:11,416 --> 00:33:12,761
He already went home.

487
00:33:14,665 --> 00:33:16,650
What an easy job, huh?

488
00:33:17,208 --> 00:33:21,293
I've been sitting here since last night.
I haven't even gone home.

489
00:33:25,313 --> 00:33:26,232
Krit.

490
00:33:44,806 --> 00:33:46,184
You've actually kept it.

491
00:33:47,562 --> 00:33:49,252
If you had no feelings,
you'd have thrown it away.

492
00:33:49,629 --> 00:33:53,256
But you kept it, so that means you
still have feelings for me, right?

493
00:33:55,503 --> 00:33:56,832
That's exactly why I'm giving it back.

494
00:33:59,343 --> 00:34:00,655
What do you actually want?

495
00:34:01,607 --> 00:34:03,576
You want me to help
with the Pixie bar, right?

496
00:34:05,578 --> 00:34:06,513
Yes.

497
00:34:08,498 --> 00:34:11,156
But more than that, I want to ask
for a chance with you, Krit.

498
00:34:13,174 --> 00:34:14,142
What chance?

499
00:34:15,537 --> 00:34:17,194
It's been gone for a long time.

500
00:34:18,162 --> 00:34:19,541
I was young back then.

501
00:34:20,558 --> 00:34:22,199
But now I know.

502
00:34:22,428 --> 00:34:25,497
The person I want to spend the rest
of my life with is you, Krit.

503
00:34:28,171 --> 00:34:29,894
Can we get back together?

504
00:34:34,143 --> 00:34:35,948
You say that like nothing ever happened.

505
00:34:37,655 --> 00:34:41,888
Didn't you leave me back then
because you wanted to become an actor?

506
00:34:43,036 --> 00:34:44,185
No, that's not it.

507
00:34:45,301 --> 00:34:47,155
I didn't leave you because of that.

508
00:34:48,878 --> 00:34:50,157
I broke up with you

509
00:34:50,978 --> 00:34:55,047
because I felt suffocated having
to hide our relationship.

510
00:34:56,983 --> 00:35:00,642
Should I fool myself into thinking
your family would accept me?

511
00:35:02,726 --> 00:35:05,646
Then why didn't you tell me
that was the reason back then?

512
00:35:08,944 --> 00:35:10,585
Would saying it have changed anything?

513
00:35:12,144 --> 00:35:13,965
Would you have had the guts
to tell your dad

514
00:35:13,965 --> 00:35:15,392
that you were dating me?

515
00:35:20,971 --> 00:35:21,890
Krit.

516
00:35:27,304 --> 00:35:28,683
Now I know.

517
00:35:29,454 --> 00:35:30,980
People aren't all the same.

518
00:35:32,112 --> 00:35:34,671
I'm ready to face
any obstacle with you, Krit.

519
00:35:35,590 --> 00:35:38,494
We can keep it a secret or tell no one.

520
00:35:39,659 --> 00:35:41,956
Just let us get back together, please.

521
00:35:48,520 --> 00:35:49,291
Pete.

522
00:35:50,357 --> 00:35:51,670
I have a boyfriend now.

523
00:35:52,228 --> 00:35:53,836
And I'm happy.

524
00:35:55,148 --> 00:35:57,659
I don't want you to come back
into his life again.

525
00:35:59,480 --> 00:36:00,382
Krit.

526
00:36:01,301 --> 00:36:03,943
Do you really think you can handle
sharing your boyfriend with others?

527
00:36:06,010 --> 00:36:08,816
You know exactly
what kind of work Wayu does.

528
00:36:11,326 --> 00:36:12,983
Worry about yourself, Pete.

529
00:36:13,361 --> 00:36:15,133
Don't worry about
other people's business.

530
00:36:19,005 --> 00:36:19,907
So, what's it going to be?

531
00:36:21,154 --> 00:36:22,549
Are you helping or not?

532
00:36:23,763 --> 00:36:26,470
Fine, I'll help.

533
00:36:26,864 --> 00:36:27,964
And after that, we're done.

534
00:36:28,882 --> 00:36:33,148
From now on, stay away from Wayu and me.

535
00:36:38,793 --> 00:36:39,629
Deal.

536
00:36:41,188 --> 00:36:42,484
As for Wayu's issue...

537
00:36:43,699 --> 00:36:47,296
Hope you can keep putting up with
sharing what's yours with others.

538
00:37:08,113 --> 00:37:10,509
I've cleared the drug issues
for the bar.

539
00:37:10,804 --> 00:37:11,805
Don't worry.

540
00:37:15,497 --> 00:37:18,384
Yeah, I have my own way.

541
00:37:19,795 --> 00:37:22,683
Pete, something big came up.

542
00:37:22,814 --> 00:37:24,669
What? What happened now?

543
00:37:24,751 --> 00:37:27,983
The tax department wants to audit us.
What should we do?

544
00:37:30,752 --> 00:37:31,314
(Krit)

545
00:37:31,314 --> 00:37:36,204
(I handled what you asked, as promised.
The tax issue is on you.)

546
00:37:36,827 --> 00:37:38,008
Darn it.

547
00:37:39,124 --> 00:37:41,519
We're done. What do we do now?

548
00:37:41,962 --> 00:37:44,489
You're the manager. Figure it out.

549
00:37:44,801 --> 00:37:46,671
- If you can't, then quit.
- Pete.

550
00:37:49,592 --> 00:37:50,757
Darn it, Krit.

551
00:37:56,270 --> 00:37:59,945
Come on, open wide, Singto.

552
00:37:59,978 --> 00:38:02,357
Ah.

553
00:38:06,918 --> 00:38:08,280
(I'll be straight with you.)

554
00:38:08,543 --> 00:38:12,152
Do you think that captain
will really take you seriously?

555
00:38:12,398 --> 00:38:14,400
Do you think someone in this kind of job

556
00:38:14,712 --> 00:38:17,485
will be loved like a normal person?

557
00:38:21,324 --> 00:38:22,899
I can't go public with this.

558
00:38:28,412 --> 00:38:29,544
Papa.

559
00:38:34,188 --> 00:38:37,486
Papa isn't coming today, sweetie.
It's just Dad.

560
00:38:39,045 --> 00:38:40,554
Why do you think I wouldn't come?

561
00:38:46,067 --> 00:38:48,889
Well... you seemed busy.

562
00:38:49,939 --> 00:38:53,926
Alright, I'm staying at home tonight.

563
00:38:54,550 --> 00:38:56,666
I want to spend some time with Singto.

564
00:38:57,520 --> 00:39:01,244
Are you mad at me for something?

565
00:39:03,197 --> 00:39:04,148
No, I'm not.

566
00:39:15,207 --> 00:39:18,981
You're not mad because I said
I can't go public about us, are you?

567
00:39:24,609 --> 00:39:25,659
No, I'm not.

568
00:39:27,907 --> 00:39:29,334
I'm your boyfriend.

569
00:39:30,253 --> 00:39:32,369
I have to respect your decision.

570
00:39:41,197 --> 00:39:43,658
So where do you want to sleep tomorrow?
At home or the condo?

571
00:39:44,363 --> 00:39:45,348
At home.

572
00:39:46,677 --> 00:39:50,746
I've got the day off tomorrow,
so I'm planning to sleep in.

573
00:39:53,995 --> 00:39:54,963
Then...

574
00:39:57,457 --> 00:40:00,541
How about we go camping
and take Singto with us?

575
00:40:01,854 --> 00:40:03,216
Don't you have to work?

576
00:40:04,118 --> 00:40:06,383
There hasn't been much progress
in the case lately.

577
00:40:06,908 --> 00:40:08,499
So I can take some time off
and be with my boyfriend.

578
00:40:11,830 --> 00:40:13,061
Shall we go camping?

579
00:40:13,635 --> 00:40:17,687
Shall we? Let's stay the night
and just relax.

580
00:40:18,081 --> 00:40:19,328
There'll be lots of fun things to do.

581
00:40:20,871 --> 00:40:24,940
But I'm not sure if Dad will want to go.

582
00:40:25,793 --> 00:40:27,548
Singto, can you try winning Dad over?

583
00:40:29,583 --> 00:40:30,518
Deal.

584
00:40:33,619 --> 00:40:34,620
Do you want to go on a trip?

585
00:40:38,640 --> 00:40:41,150
Mm, okay. Let's go, then.

586
00:40:44,350 --> 00:40:48,157
We're going on a trip!
We're really going!

587
00:40:50,404 --> 00:40:53,538
Then you've got to eat lots, okay?

588
00:40:54,277 --> 00:40:55,310
Okay, come on.

589
00:40:56,885 --> 00:40:58,264
Mm.

590
00:41:00,003 --> 00:41:01,972
Want some water? Just a sip.

591
00:41:02,005 --> 00:41:03,055
Here you go.

592
00:41:05,237 --> 00:41:06,848
Dip it all the way in.

593
00:41:07,222 --> 00:41:08,879
It's all gone!

594
00:41:09,470 --> 00:41:10,619
Whoa.

595
00:41:11,669 --> 00:41:14,464
Having fun in the water, Singto? Hmm?

596
00:41:15,820 --> 00:41:16,804
Soaked through now.

597
00:41:16,804 --> 00:41:17,728
Gosh.

598
00:41:17,728 --> 00:41:19,462
Let me dry your hair first.

599
00:41:19,462 --> 00:41:20,736
Let me dry your hair first.

600
00:41:20,736 --> 00:41:21,989
Dinner's here.

601
00:41:22,498 --> 00:41:23,876
Are you hungry? Are you hungry yet?

602
00:41:24,057 --> 00:41:26,797
Hungry now? Oh, you are?

603
00:41:27,633 --> 00:41:29,816
Let Papa do it for you. Just a sec.

604
00:41:29,816 --> 00:41:32,146
Wipe it first. Wipe.

605
00:41:34,164 --> 00:41:35,280
- Is it nice?
- Is it nice?

606
00:41:35,280 --> 00:41:36,526
What's that? Stick it on.

607
00:41:37,593 --> 00:41:39,742
- Come.
- Peel it off first.

608
00:41:43,139 --> 00:41:47,175
- Better here. Yeah.
- Yeah.

609
00:41:49,570 --> 00:41:52,163
Whoa, good job.

610
00:41:52,163 --> 00:41:55,280
Which patterns can Dad pick?
Let me see. What's this?

611
00:42:05,223 --> 00:42:06,618
Singto's asleep now.

612
00:42:07,110 --> 00:42:08,899
He must've worn out
playing in the water.

613
00:42:10,162 --> 00:42:11,015
Huh.

614
00:42:25,553 --> 00:42:28,129
Thank you for taking me
and Singto on this trip.

615
00:42:29,228 --> 00:42:32,427
I've wanted to bring Singto here
for so long, but had no chance.

616
00:42:36,332 --> 00:42:39,712
You don't need to thank me.
I wanted to bring you here anyway.

617
00:42:48,687 --> 00:42:49,737
I'm sorry.

618
00:42:50,820 --> 00:42:52,166
About not being able to go public.

619
00:42:55,940 --> 00:42:57,695
It's not because I have someone else.

620
00:42:58,614 --> 00:43:02,224
It's because of my family.
My parents can't accept it.

621
00:43:03,963 --> 00:43:06,949
They still don't know how you are?

622
00:43:09,952 --> 00:43:12,971
Do you think General Pitak
could accept this?

623
00:43:16,154 --> 00:43:20,010
My dad is strict
and has too high expectations.

624
00:43:21,355 --> 00:43:23,751
He'd never accept that I like you, Wayu.

625
00:43:28,689 --> 00:43:29,854
I don't want to hide this.

626
00:43:31,101 --> 00:43:32,922
But I want to handle this myself.

627
00:43:33,743 --> 00:43:35,302
Knowing would only burden you.

628
00:43:41,389 --> 00:43:43,653
Coming out means a lot to me.

629
00:43:46,344 --> 00:43:48,674
I know. I can tell.

630
00:43:51,906 --> 00:43:56,861
I don't know. Having someone I really love
and not being able to tell anyone.

631
00:43:57,403 --> 00:44:00,176
It makes me feel so insecure.

632
00:44:05,164 --> 00:44:06,279
You can be sure of one thing.

633
00:44:07,297 --> 00:44:09,905
You're the only one I love.

634
00:44:14,975 --> 00:44:16,075
You know,

635
00:44:16,682 --> 00:44:18,601
before I became a host,

636
00:44:19,947 --> 00:44:24,426
I used to dream of having
a normal college romance.

637
00:44:24,968 --> 00:44:27,987
At this age, I should have a boyfriend.
At this age, I should know heartbreak.

638
00:44:28,200 --> 00:44:30,399
At this age, I should be
doing an internship.

639
00:44:33,171 --> 00:44:35,206
But with the way my life has been,

640
00:44:36,486 --> 00:44:38,881
I'm afraid to even dream

641
00:44:40,046 --> 00:44:43,541
that I could have a normal relationship
like everyone else.

642
00:44:46,232 --> 00:44:48,267
If your parents are your obstacle,

643
00:44:50,711 --> 00:44:53,156
my mom is an obstacle for me too.

644
00:44:58,390 --> 00:44:59,801
I'm sorry

645
00:45:00,474 --> 00:45:02,279
for picking a fight without knowing

646
00:45:02,623 --> 00:45:03,969
what you'd been through.

647
00:45:05,970 --> 00:45:07,020
It's okay.

648
00:45:08,678 --> 00:45:11,631
If you get mad,
I'll just make it up to you.

649
00:45:15,306 --> 00:45:16,717
I won't let go for sure.

650
00:45:21,590 --> 00:45:23,592
Let's hold hands
and get through this together.

651
00:45:25,085 --> 00:45:28,154
Besides, I've got you now.

652
00:45:29,040 --> 00:45:30,401
You can't get away from me.

653
00:45:34,569 --> 00:45:36,587
Then you'd better hold on to me tight.

654
00:45:37,736 --> 00:45:38,835
Of course.

655
00:45:44,381 --> 00:45:46,678
Come on. Have a little more
before it gets cold.

656
00:45:47,908 --> 00:45:49,221
I really can't anymore.

657
00:45:49,221 --> 00:45:50,632
Here, I'll get some for you.

658
00:45:51,502 --> 00:45:53,537
- Just vegetables are fine.
- Here, have some pork.

659
00:45:53,537 --> 00:45:54,997
- I really can't anymore.
- Here.

660
00:46:09,376 --> 00:46:14,592
(Mind: Are you coming
to the bar on Monday?)

661
00:46:17,213 --> 00:46:18,819
You've been talking to this person
a lot lately.

662
00:46:20,724 --> 00:46:22,922
Oh, just a customer. It's nothing.

663
00:46:24,563 --> 00:46:27,681
You don't talk this much
with your other customers.

664
00:46:29,764 --> 00:46:31,470
This customer's name is Mind.

665
00:46:31,470 --> 00:46:34,194
We're the same age and go to
the same university.

666
00:46:34,194 --> 00:46:36,131
So we have a lot to talk about.

667
00:46:38,428 --> 00:46:39,494
A friend from university?

668
00:46:40,315 --> 00:46:44,236
Yes, but we actually met
when he came in as a customer.

669
00:46:44,433 --> 00:46:46,992
On his first day, he booked
100 drinks with me.

670
00:46:46,992 --> 00:46:50,750
Then we found out we're from
the same university. Small world.

671
00:46:52,144 --> 00:46:53,867
Are you sure he's not hitting on you?

672
00:46:55,246 --> 00:46:56,443
Come on.

673
00:46:57,756 --> 00:46:59,790
I'm not that naive.

674
00:47:00,693 --> 00:47:05,107
And besides, Krit, I'd never cross
the line with a customer.

675
00:47:09,471 --> 00:47:11,161
Then keep your distance a little.

676
00:47:11,768 --> 00:47:15,214
Replying to his chats often
is a bit annoying.

677
00:47:17,905 --> 00:47:19,004
Alright!

678
00:47:38,020 --> 00:47:39,136
Mind if I sit?

679
00:47:48,000 --> 00:47:48,832
Hello, Mom.

680
00:47:49,024 --> 00:47:49,600
Ice.

681
00:47:49,600 --> 00:47:52,295
Yeah, I'm almost at work.

682
00:47:52,672 --> 00:47:55,264
Alright, I'll let you know then.

683
00:47:55,456 --> 00:47:55,987
This is...

684
00:47:55,987 --> 00:47:58,710
I already ate. Have you eaten yet, Mom?

685
00:47:58,710 --> 00:48:00,385
- Oh. Okay.
- Alright.

686
00:48:00,385 --> 00:48:02,402
Okay.

687
00:48:04,000 --> 00:48:04,672
Clean.

688
00:48:05,856 --> 00:48:06,400
Here.

689
00:48:08,670 --> 00:48:10,426
Long time no see.

690
00:48:11,984 --> 00:48:15,052
This is Ice, a new customer
from Singapore.

691
00:48:15,360 --> 00:48:15,936
Hey!

692
00:48:16,064 --> 00:48:18,597
Whoa, Wayu. What's got you so startled?

693
00:48:19,926 --> 00:48:20,795
Bro.

694
00:48:22,288 --> 00:48:24,782
Oh, are you a host here?

695
00:48:24,979 --> 00:48:27,571
No, I quit being a host.

696
00:48:27,571 --> 00:48:28,448
Just hang out.

697
00:48:28,960 --> 00:48:29,852
Oh.

698
00:48:29,852 --> 00:48:32,428
How've you been? It's been a while.

699
00:48:32,428 --> 00:48:34,692
I'm good, bro. Really good.

700
00:48:35,712 --> 00:48:36,992
Are you... okay?

701
00:48:37,504 --> 00:48:38,597
Are you looking for someone?

702
00:48:39,287 --> 00:48:41,797
No, not really.

703
00:48:42,765 --> 00:48:44,750
Alright, I should get back to work.

704
00:48:44,768 --> 00:48:46,016
Sure. See you around.

705
00:48:46,016 --> 00:48:46,720
See you, bro.

706
00:48:46,720 --> 00:48:47,392
Bye-bye.

707
00:48:59,714 --> 00:49:00,649
Hello, Krit.

708
00:49:01,076 --> 00:49:03,012
Nut has started making his move.

709
00:49:03,012 --> 00:49:05,178
I followed him, but we got separated.

710
00:49:05,178 --> 00:49:06,261
I can't see him now.

711
00:49:06,687 --> 00:49:08,181
Why were you following him?

712
00:49:09,116 --> 00:49:10,806
You aren't an informant for me anymore.

713
00:49:11,856 --> 00:49:13,710
Did he notice you?

714
00:49:14,219 --> 00:49:15,384
No, he didn't.

715
00:49:16,630 --> 00:49:17,500
Okay.

716
00:49:19,485 --> 00:49:21,520
Wayu, just go back to work like normal.

717
00:49:21,984 --> 00:49:24,227
If you see him again, just let me know.

718
00:49:24,506 --> 00:49:27,197
Don't go following him around
like that, okay?

719
00:49:28,460 --> 00:49:29,314
Okay.

720
00:49:30,183 --> 00:49:32,973
Why are you scolding me?

721
00:49:32,973 --> 00:49:34,892
I just wanted to help.

722
00:49:38,617 --> 00:49:42,276
- Sorry, I was just worried...
- Captain.

723
00:49:42,473 --> 00:49:43,539
Captain.

724
00:49:43,539 --> 00:49:44,819
Captain, this is bad.

725
00:49:45,278 --> 00:49:46,082
Yes.

726
00:49:49,052 --> 00:49:51,513
Chainphop was murdered in prison.

727
00:49:51,513 --> 00:49:52,268
What?

728
00:49:53,334 --> 00:49:54,106
And then...

729
00:49:54,992 --> 00:49:56,124
Have you found the suspect yet?

730
00:49:56,124 --> 00:49:58,618
Not yet, Captain.
But we're working on it.

731
00:50:00,455 --> 00:50:03,228
There's one more thing, Captain.

732
00:50:03,803 --> 00:50:07,215
(Rudy Talks)
Hello, you can call me Por.

733
00:50:07,642 --> 00:50:10,563
Por's been appearing on a lot of shows
like this lately.

734
00:50:10,563 --> 00:50:14,041
Most of them are produced by Supanut.

735
00:50:14,746 --> 00:50:17,109
Our source reports
that the two of them have been

736
00:50:17,109 --> 00:50:18,389
secretly meeting quite often.

737
00:50:18,602 --> 00:50:20,309
Looks like he's become the favorite.

738
00:50:20,768 --> 00:50:22,573
After all, he helped him
get out of several cases.

739
00:50:24,624 --> 00:50:26,905
Sergeant, keep an eye on Supanut.

740
00:50:26,905 --> 00:50:29,202
Por may be using Supanut
instead of Chain now.

741
00:50:29,202 --> 00:50:30,350
Yes, Captain.

742
00:50:30,383 --> 00:50:32,155
Sergeant, head out to the field with me.

743
00:50:32,256 --> 00:50:33,280
Lieutenant, go.

744
00:50:33,280 --> 00:50:34,016
Let's go, everyone.

745
00:50:34,016 --> 00:50:34,688
(Drug Case Suspect)

746
00:50:37,216 --> 00:50:40,544
(Chainphop Udomdirek, 32,
Owner of C Group Logistic export business)

747
00:50:40,544 --> 00:50:41,984
(Drug Case Suspect)

748
00:50:42,176 --> 00:50:45,088
(Supanut Tosakan, 32,
Famous TV producer)

749
00:50:54,059 --> 00:50:55,241
- Hey, Tai.
- Hmm?

750
00:50:55,241 --> 00:50:58,686
Why are you working out?
You're not competing next week, right?

751
00:50:59,425 --> 00:51:02,903
Come on. Sports Day's coming up.

752
00:51:02,985 --> 00:51:05,413
I don't want to lose to Sky's team.

753
00:51:05,856 --> 00:51:07,743
I saw him sneaking off
to practice the other day.

754
00:51:09,204 --> 00:51:12,337
But we're playing soccer, man.
Why are you training arm muscles?

755
00:51:12,485 --> 00:51:15,094
Come on! Haven't you heard about this?

756
00:51:15,094 --> 00:51:17,637
Train your arms
to support your legs, man.

757
00:51:17,637 --> 00:51:20,328
Don't you know about balance?

758
00:51:20,623 --> 00:51:21,542
Sigh.

759
00:51:23,035 --> 00:51:25,300
- Come on, you idiot.
- Let me eat first.

760
00:51:31,731 --> 00:51:33,241
- Hey, Tai.
- Hm?

761
00:51:33,241 --> 00:51:35,128
How long have you been
with your girlfriend?

762
00:51:39,574 --> 00:51:40,674
Five years.

763
00:51:41,100 --> 00:51:42,954
- Five years?
- Mm.

764
00:51:44,382 --> 00:51:48,287
When your girlfriend gets bored of you
or starts getting annoyed with you,

765
00:51:48,894 --> 00:51:49,862
what does she do?

766
00:51:51,978 --> 00:51:54,604
Well... She gets irritated.

767
00:51:55,736 --> 00:51:57,147
She doesn't really talk to me.

768
00:51:57,409 --> 00:52:00,921
She stops asking me to help with things
she used to ask me to do.

769
00:52:01,200 --> 00:52:02,364
Something like that, I guess.

770
00:52:03,283 --> 00:52:05,187
Wow, spot on.

771
00:52:05,564 --> 00:52:06,499
What do you mean?

772
00:52:07,730 --> 00:52:10,732
What you just said is exactly
what Captain's been doing to me.

773
00:52:14,227 --> 00:52:15,934
Has it been a while since you got laid?

774
00:52:18,526 --> 00:52:19,986
What does that kind of thing
have to do with it?

775
00:52:19,986 --> 00:52:22,940
Hey, that's the very thing

776
00:52:22,940 --> 00:52:25,860
that bonds a love relationship.

777
00:52:29,519 --> 00:52:31,061
So what should I do?

778
00:52:31,767 --> 00:52:33,982
You've got to spice things up.

779
00:52:34,130 --> 00:52:35,885
- Spice things up?
- Mm-hmm.

780
00:52:36,296 --> 00:52:37,428
How?

781
00:52:43,728 --> 00:52:45,894
Tai, what are you doing?

782
00:52:46,288 --> 00:52:48,290
Hmm, try this.

783
00:52:58,976 --> 00:52:59,712
Whoa.

784
00:52:59,936 --> 00:53:01,153
How is it?

785
00:53:01,153 --> 00:53:03,975
Yeah, that's it.
It needs to be this spicy.

786
00:53:04,254 --> 00:53:05,747
Then what?

787
00:53:06,125 --> 00:53:07,487
It's not hard, buddy.

788
00:53:08,044 --> 00:53:10,276
Come here. Move in closer.

789
00:53:11,211 --> 00:53:12,992
I'll tell you how.

790
00:54:15,693 --> 00:54:16,957
You got me, Officer.

791
00:54:18,351 --> 00:54:19,418
I'm all yours.

792
00:54:26,096 --> 00:54:27,294
You criminal.

793
00:54:28,278 --> 00:54:30,976
You know that, right? Doing this,

794
00:54:32,416 --> 00:54:33,344
you're not getting away with it.

795
00:54:47,344 --> 00:54:48,320
Mm.

796
00:54:57,976 --> 00:54:59,846
I'm going to need to search you.

797
00:55:33,187 --> 00:55:34,680
I'm placing you under arrest

798
00:55:35,894 --> 00:55:37,699
for soliciting a public officer.

799
00:56:13,500 --> 00:56:14,468
Hmm.

800
00:56:40,524 --> 00:56:43,395
Hehe.

801
00:56:44,298 --> 00:56:45,069
Hehe.

802
00:56:47,349 --> 00:56:49,843
And Foei actually bought
the food poisoning story?

803
00:56:50,959 --> 00:56:51,665
Hehe.

804
00:56:52,649 --> 00:56:55,225
Honestly, I should thank Tai.

805
00:56:55,225 --> 00:56:58,769
He really sold it,
so Foei believed I was actually sick.

806
00:57:02,379 --> 00:57:03,527
And...

807
00:57:05,316 --> 00:57:09,828
That little sweet act just now
was Tai's idea too.

808
00:57:11,272 --> 00:57:12,125
Really?

809
00:57:13,274 --> 00:57:14,406
That explains it.

810
00:57:17,753 --> 00:57:19,180
So why'd you come up with that idea?

811
00:57:22,429 --> 00:57:23,348
Well...

812
00:57:24,431 --> 00:57:27,450
I feel like we haven't been

813
00:57:30,305 --> 00:57:31,732
as sweet lately,

814
00:57:32,290 --> 00:57:35,129
so I wanted to spice things up.

815
00:57:37,311 --> 00:57:38,673
Who put that idea in your head?

816
00:57:40,084 --> 00:57:42,118
The reason I haven't been
following you much

817
00:57:42,463 --> 00:57:46,237
is that I had Rose
hire someone to buy you drinks.

818
00:57:47,008 --> 00:57:50,043
That way, I know exactly where you are
and what you're doing at all times.

819
00:57:51,569 --> 00:57:53,768
You actually hired someone
to buy drinks for me?

820
00:57:55,605 --> 00:57:57,328
Well, you told me not to go to the bar.

821
00:57:57,328 --> 00:57:59,264
But you never said
I wasn't allowed to do this.

822
00:58:00,314 --> 00:58:02,267
Whoa, that explains it.

823
00:58:02,267 --> 00:58:04,613
I was wondering why my customers
have been so nice lately.

824
00:58:04,613 --> 00:58:07,239
They weren't handsy with me at all.
I'm honestly confused,

825
00:58:07,239 --> 00:58:08,896
like, how is that possible?

826
00:58:10,028 --> 00:58:11,275
Does that usually happen?

827
00:58:13,112 --> 00:58:16,804
Well, sometimes. That's just
how drunk people are.

828
00:58:17,329 --> 00:58:18,002
Hey.

829
00:58:18,921 --> 00:58:23,497
Even if people can meet me or touch me,

830
00:58:24,844 --> 00:58:26,255
you don't have to worry.

831
00:58:26,665 --> 00:58:30,636
No one can take me away,
because I'm yours alone.

832
00:58:32,162 --> 00:58:33,130
Yeah.

833
00:58:35,000 --> 00:58:36,280
You're all mine.

834
00:58:38,511 --> 00:58:39,414
Oh.

835
00:58:42,367 --> 00:58:43,713
Hey.

836
00:58:44,894 --> 00:58:46,814
You're marking your territory?

837
00:58:47,880 --> 00:58:48,733
Yeah.

838
00:58:50,391 --> 00:58:53,262
Hey, let me tell you something.

839
00:58:53,262 --> 00:58:56,330
From now on, you don't need
to hire someone to keep an eye on me.

840
00:58:56,724 --> 00:59:00,662
I already asked Foei to send
only good customers my way.

841
00:59:00,662 --> 00:59:03,697
So he'll screen them for me anyway.

842
00:59:03,993 --> 00:59:05,010
You don't need to worry.

843
00:59:08,079 --> 00:59:08,932
I don't know.

844
00:59:10,392 --> 00:59:13,985
What don't you know?
You're making me uncomfortable.

845
00:59:17,020 --> 00:59:19,793
Fine. I won't do it anymore.

846
00:59:21,483 --> 00:59:24,190
Good boy.

847
00:59:30,261 --> 00:59:34,248
Oh, and tomorrow,
I've got an outside job.

848
00:59:36,496 --> 00:59:37,448
Where are you going?

849
00:59:38,367 --> 00:59:39,318
With whom?

850
00:59:39,597 --> 00:59:41,911
With Mind, like I told you before.

851
00:59:43,256 --> 00:59:45,881
Again? That name again?

852
00:59:46,472 --> 00:59:47,522
Come on.

853
00:59:48,868 --> 00:59:51,542
He's a regular, and he's my friend.

854
00:59:51,542 --> 00:59:55,283
But don't worry. I'm not
going alone with Mind.

855
00:59:56,120 --> 00:59:57,875
His friends are coming too.

856
01:00:00,386 --> 01:00:01,666
Hey.

857
01:00:03,602 --> 01:00:06,496
Don't worry. I'll keep you updated
every step of the way.

858
01:00:06,496 --> 01:00:08,179
Wherever I go, whatever I'm doing...

859
01:00:08,475 --> 01:00:09,443
Okay?

860
01:00:10,821 --> 01:00:14,840
Oh... Put this on.

861
01:00:18,581 --> 01:00:19,615
Cute.

862
01:00:29,344 --> 01:00:30,656
I'm not wearing it anymore.

863
01:00:30,656 --> 01:00:32,512
Mm-mm. Don't.

864
01:00:46,721 --> 01:00:47,673
Go.

865
01:00:49,035 --> 01:00:50,692
- Wow.
- It's too high.

866
01:00:50,921 --> 01:00:53,333
- Watch.
- Try again.

867
01:00:53,333 --> 01:00:54,154
Okay.

868
01:00:55,877 --> 01:00:56,763
Ah.

869
01:00:57,567 --> 01:00:59,273
Oh, wow.

870
01:00:59,831 --> 01:01:02,751
Sorry, Mind. It's my first time playing.

871
01:01:02,784 --> 01:01:03,488
I'm really bad at this.

872
01:01:03,904 --> 01:01:05,967
It's okay. It's your first time.

873
01:01:05,967 --> 01:01:06,848
Yeah.

874
01:01:07,456 --> 01:01:08,264
So then...

875
01:01:08,896 --> 01:01:09,536
Want me to teach you?

876
01:01:09,984 --> 01:01:10,857
Sure.

877
01:01:11,480 --> 01:01:13,318
Come on. Let's make sure
I hit it this time.

878
01:01:28,282 --> 01:01:29,824
- Come here.
- Come on.

879
01:01:29,890 --> 01:01:32,000
Wayu, try standing here.

880
01:01:32,000 --> 01:01:33,122
Hmm.

881
01:01:33,122 --> 01:01:34,302
Look ahead

882
01:01:34,302 --> 01:01:36,010
- Uh-huh.
- and reach your racket out.

883
01:01:37,142 --> 01:01:39,357
Like this, and use your left hand.

884
01:01:39,357 --> 01:01:42,064
Your left hand goes on top. Then...

885
01:01:42,064 --> 01:01:44,361
Bend both knees. Lower a little more.

886
01:01:44,837 --> 01:01:47,552
Okay, now let go with your left hand.

887
01:01:48,020 --> 01:01:50,284
Release your left hand and reach back.

888
01:01:51,531 --> 01:01:54,140
Right here. Then step left.

889
01:01:54,747 --> 01:01:56,043
- Step left.
- Get ready.

890
01:01:56,043 --> 01:01:58,357
- Mm-hmm.
- Then swing. Whoosh.

891
01:01:59,358 --> 01:02:01,113
- Like this, is it right?
- Mm-hmm.

892
01:02:08,038 --> 01:02:09,727
Yeah, like this?

893
01:02:09,727 --> 01:02:10,912
- Yeah, just like that.
- Hmm.

894
01:02:11,552 --> 01:02:12,224
Okay.

895
01:02:15,060 --> 01:02:18,079
Then should we take a break first?

896
01:02:19,080 --> 01:02:21,607
Sounds good. Kind of sore.

897
01:02:22,099 --> 01:02:24,002
Yeah, let's go.

898
01:02:27,070 --> 01:02:28,613
- Sigh.
- Mm.

899
01:02:31,840 --> 01:02:32,512
Woo.

900
01:02:33,440 --> 01:02:34,437
It really hurts.

901
01:02:35,668 --> 01:02:37,391
How was it? Did you have fun?

902
01:02:37,785 --> 01:02:39,097
I had fun today, Mind.

903
01:02:40,229 --> 01:02:43,314
But I think if more friends had come,

904
01:02:43,314 --> 01:02:44,643
it would've been even more fun.

905
01:02:45,234 --> 01:02:46,842
They were all busy.

906
01:02:47,268 --> 01:02:48,696
And they only told me last minute.

907
01:02:50,008 --> 01:02:50,944
Lonely?

908
01:02:50,944 --> 01:02:52,223
Hey, no.

909
01:02:52,666 --> 01:02:55,505
It's okay, Mind. I'm happy being
this kind of friend to you.

910
01:02:59,082 --> 01:02:59,837
Oh, right.

911
01:03:00,608 --> 01:03:02,232
I brought something for you too, Wayu.

912
01:03:02,938 --> 01:03:03,873
Really?

913
01:03:10,042 --> 01:03:11,273
Wow, Mind.

914
01:03:11,535 --> 01:03:13,389
Hey, thank you so much, but...

915
01:03:13,408 --> 01:03:15,200
I can't accept this. It's too expensive.

916
01:03:15,200 --> 01:03:16,523
It's okay.

917
01:03:16,687 --> 01:03:19,526
I thought it'd suit you,
so I wanted you to have it.

918
01:03:24,005 --> 01:03:27,352
Sometimes when I go somewhere,

919
01:03:28,583 --> 01:03:31,553
I catch myself wishing
you were there with me too.

920
01:03:33,177 --> 01:03:34,506
I think you'd like it too.

921
01:03:39,855 --> 01:03:41,791
Here. It looks perfect on you.

922
01:03:43,399 --> 01:03:44,236
Hmm.

923
01:03:46,533 --> 01:03:47,927
I never

924
01:03:48,879 --> 01:03:49,617
believed in

925
01:03:51,340 --> 01:03:52,735
"Love at first sight"

926
01:03:55,787 --> 01:03:57,411
until I met you, Wayu.

927
01:03:58,953 --> 01:04:00,578
At the registrar's office at university.

928
01:04:02,087 --> 01:04:03,531
Dropping those earbuds

929
01:04:04,795 --> 01:04:06,468
must have been fate.

930
01:04:08,552 --> 01:04:10,176
- Hee-hee.
- I...

931
01:04:11,833 --> 01:04:13,015
I like you, Wayu.

932
01:04:15,377 --> 01:04:16,526
I really do.

933
01:04:17,100 --> 01:04:18,807
I liked you even before

934
01:04:19,397 --> 01:04:20,694
I knew you worked as a host.

935
01:04:22,334 --> 01:04:26,354
From now on, I want to support you
in everything.

936
01:04:28,356 --> 01:04:29,849
Everything you want to do.

937
01:04:31,539 --> 01:04:32,507
So...

938
01:04:35,312 --> 01:04:38,198
Will you be my boyfriend, Wayu?

939
01:04:44,704 --> 01:04:47,651
You don't have to answer right away.
I understand.

940
01:04:51,967 --> 01:04:54,018
No, it's okay, Mind.

941
01:04:54,854 --> 01:04:56,462
I'd rather answer you now.

942
01:04:58,398 --> 01:05:01,188
I'm really grateful
that you have good feelings for me.

943
01:05:03,550 --> 01:05:06,701
But I can't return your feelings.

944
01:05:25,012 --> 01:05:26,177
I'm sorry, Mind.

945
01:05:26,965 --> 01:05:28,885
I'm already in a serious relationship.

946
01:05:30,032 --> 01:05:34,085
♪I can only be someone you know♪

947
01:05:34,085 --> 01:05:37,137
♪Not the one you love♪

948
01:05:37,137 --> 01:05:37,941
But...

949
01:05:39,286 --> 01:05:42,752
We can still be friends, right?

950
01:05:46,653 --> 01:05:48,803
Are you really okay
with just being friends with me?

951
01:05:53,020 --> 01:05:56,022
Of course. I mean it.

952
01:05:57,696 --> 01:05:58,752
Friends it is.

953
01:06:01,601 --> 01:06:02,815
I'm good.

954
01:06:08,508 --> 01:06:11,281
Then... as your friend...

955
01:06:12,348 --> 01:06:14,760
can you take this heartbroken friend
out for a pity drink?

956
01:06:15,006 --> 01:06:15,974
Haha.

957
01:06:17,385 --> 01:06:18,255
Sure.

958
01:06:19,682 --> 01:06:22,586
Then how about Moonlit?

959
01:06:23,456 --> 01:06:24,572
I'll book us a table.

960
01:06:27,180 --> 01:06:30,856
Sounds good. Book it.
Drink until we drop.

961
01:06:31,660 --> 01:06:32,972
- Come on.
- Let's go.

962
01:06:33,497 --> 01:06:34,465
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

963
01:06:36,672 --> 01:06:39,847
♪There's still someone like me
who could die in your place♪

964
01:06:39,847 --> 01:06:43,161
♪I'll keep loving you
until you see the real world♪

965
01:06:43,161 --> 01:06:46,427
♪Where a princess
may never find her prince♪

966
01:06:46,427 --> 01:06:55,488
♪In real life, even if that's hard
for you to understand♪

967
01:07:03,210 --> 01:07:09,200
♪Even if you'll never understand me♪

968
01:07:09,263 --> 01:07:10,333
Whose scent is this?

969
01:07:12,498 --> 01:07:15,058
(Do you really think you can handle
sharing your boyfriend with others?)

970
01:07:16,272 --> 01:07:17,470
You know exactly

971
01:07:17,470 --> 01:07:19,111
what kind of work Wayu does.

972
01:07:35,256 --> 01:07:37,225
Oh, stop walking already.
My head's killing me.

973
01:07:38,980 --> 01:07:39,801
Hey.

974
01:07:40,736 --> 01:07:43,164
For someone's perfume
to get on your clothes,

975
01:07:43,164 --> 01:07:44,838
you have to be really close
to them, right?

976
01:07:45,265 --> 01:07:48,201
Yeah, that's right. Why?

977
01:07:48,825 --> 01:07:51,056
I smelled some stranger's perfume
on Wayu's shirt.

978
01:07:51,729 --> 01:07:55,306
It's probably that guy Mind's perfume.
He's one of Wayu's regulars.

979
01:07:55,487 --> 01:07:58,571
They've been chatting a lot lately.
I wonder what they talk about so much.

980
01:07:59,785 --> 01:08:01,508
Have you asked Wayu yet?

981
01:08:03,920 --> 01:08:05,610
He went out on a job
with that person today.

982
01:08:06,578 --> 01:08:09,564
At first, he said
he was going with friends.

983
01:08:10,139 --> 01:08:13,338
But I found out it ended up
being just the two of them.

984
01:08:15,898 --> 01:08:18,195
Perfume getting on someone's shirt
is pretty normal.

985
01:08:18,753 --> 01:08:19,934
You know what his job is like.

986
01:08:19,934 --> 01:08:21,968
The place is loud, so they have to talk
closely, right?

987
01:08:22,904 --> 01:08:26,333
From what I had someone check,
Wayu's good at taking care of himself.

988
01:08:26,333 --> 01:08:27,317
So don't worry.

989
01:08:31,222 --> 01:08:34,373
We can't go public, and I can't
even visit him at work.

990
01:08:34,373 --> 01:08:35,472
I can't pick him up.

991
01:08:36,046 --> 01:08:37,507
I can't do anything at all.

992
01:08:39,689 --> 01:08:42,625
But you can't go public either,
so it's a draw, right?

993
01:08:53,340 --> 01:08:58,164
(Wayu: I'm at Moonlit.
I'm here drinking with Mind)

994
01:08:58,164 --> 01:09:01,380
Going out together wasn't enough.
Now they're drinking too?

995
01:09:03,201 --> 01:09:04,678
- Hey, buddy.
- Move aside.

996
01:09:09,824 --> 01:09:10,528
Hi.

997
01:09:11,744 --> 01:09:12,668
You made it there already?

998
01:09:13,489 --> 01:09:17,049
Yeah, I'm here.
Just getting drinks for Mind.

999
01:09:17,049 --> 01:09:20,806
But it looks like
it's going to be a long night.

1000
01:09:21,135 --> 01:09:23,579
Why? I thought you said
you were only traveling.

1001
01:09:25,351 --> 01:09:26,943
Uh...

1002
01:09:28,239 --> 01:09:29,158
Well...

1003
01:09:30,585 --> 01:09:32,932
He suddenly confessed
his feelings to me.

1004
01:09:33,851 --> 01:09:36,738
But don't worry.
I already turned him down.

1005
01:09:36,738 --> 01:09:39,511
I told him I already
have a boyfriend, so...

1006
01:09:39,708 --> 01:09:43,694
I'm drinking with him
to cheer him up, but I'm not alone.

1007
01:09:43,694 --> 01:09:48,206
I'm here with Foei, Tai,
and all the others from the place.

1008
01:09:48,782 --> 01:09:49,963
When will you be home?

1009
01:09:50,619 --> 01:09:54,016
Around 2 AM.
I won't let it be any later.

1010
01:09:54,720 --> 01:09:56,352
Okay, I'll wait up.

1011
01:09:56,992 --> 01:09:58,872
Okay. See you later.

1012
01:10:02,269 --> 01:10:03,237
Hey.

1013
01:10:03,844 --> 01:10:06,633
Good. At least you were reasonable
and didn't take it out on him.

1014
01:10:06,863 --> 01:10:09,554
But I'm telling you,
Mind's not done yet.

1015
01:10:10,407 --> 01:10:13,492
Even after Wayu turned him down,
they're still drinking together.

1016
01:10:16,543 --> 01:10:19,644
So what are you going to do?
Go drag him back from the bar?

1017
01:10:21,810 --> 01:10:22,713
I don't know.

1018
01:10:22,942 --> 01:10:25,010
But I don't trust those people
who approach Wayu.

1019
01:10:28,160 --> 01:10:28,898
Sigh.

1020
01:10:39,416 --> 01:10:45,404
Alright, see you again at Moonlit.
That's all for tonight. Goodbye.

1021
01:10:48,571 --> 01:10:50,392
I'm not going home! No way!

1022
01:10:50,392 --> 01:10:52,706
Over here! Three of you. Three!

1023
01:10:52,837 --> 01:10:55,659
- Whoa, come on.
- Over here, this way.

1024
01:10:55,938 --> 01:10:58,006
- Ugh.
- So worth it!

1025
01:10:58,481 --> 01:11:00,747
- Oh.
- Hello.

1026
01:11:00,747 --> 01:11:02,239
- Take it.
- Okay.

1027
01:11:04,372 --> 01:11:06,751
Go!

1028
01:11:06,752 --> 01:11:07,456
Want to play a game?

1029
01:11:07,872 --> 01:11:09,458
- A game?
- Yeah, let's play! Play!

1030
01:11:09,458 --> 01:11:10,912
Come on!

1031
01:11:11,296 --> 01:11:12,352
- Come on! Let's play a game.
- Where are you going?

1032
01:11:12,789 --> 01:11:14,304
Careful. Watch your step, Mind.

1033
01:11:14,304 --> 01:11:15,296
What game is it?

1034
01:11:15,808 --> 01:11:16,736
The bill-biting game.

1035
01:11:16,832 --> 01:11:18,909
The bill-biting game? Uh... Okay.

1036
01:11:19,943 --> 01:11:22,650
Come on. Uh... Mind.

1037
01:11:23,392 --> 01:11:25,152
Mm.

1038
01:11:25,504 --> 01:11:27,571
Come on. Hurry up.

1039
01:11:27,648 --> 01:11:28,800
Mind.

1040
01:11:28,800 --> 01:11:30,837
Come on!

1041
01:11:31,008 --> 01:11:31,616
Come on...

1042
01:11:31,648 --> 01:11:33,728
Uh... Slowly.

1043
01:11:34,688 --> 01:11:35,840
Hey!

1044
01:11:35,872 --> 01:11:36,992
- Hey!
- Hey!

1045
01:11:40,223 --> 01:11:41,141
Krit.

1046
01:11:42,569 --> 01:11:43,980
I came to take you home.

1047
